Drivers are being warned to expect delays on the M80 near Cumbernauld after a five vehicle crash. Delays after five vehicle crash Drivers are being warned to expect delays on the M80 near Cumbernauld after a five vehicle crash.Traffic Scotland said the accident initially closed one of the southbound carriageways before moving to the hard shoulder.The accident, which happened between junctions 6 and 6a, was reported shortly before 7.30am.Drivers are warned traffic is &quot;very heavy&quot; and to expect short delays. 